main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects were reported near Gander, Newfoundland, in June and July 1956.
interesting points: A civilian airline pilot reported an unidentified object drifting white to blue green, which flashed white light and moved faster than any aircraft., A crew from a Stratocruiser aircraft sighted a bright, pulsating light moving at high speed, estimated 3 to 5 miles away., The objects in the second sighting changed direction rapidly and accelerated rapidly to speeds over 1,500 mph., Another report mentioned an object leaving an area at high speed, approximately 175 feet long., Radar confirmed visual contact with unknown objects moving at speeds in excess of 6,000 mph in the same region.
witness description: civilian airline pilot and crew members of a Stratocruiser aircraft
